{
  "name": "Medical Release Investiture of Acid",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Medical.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You draw out acidic chakra and infuse it into yourself, coating your entire body like armor. The acid does not harm you. You cannot lose concentration on this jutsu as a result of damage. For the duration, you gain the following benefits;</p><p>• You are immune to Acid, Poison, and Cold Damage.</p><p>• You have resistance to Bludgeoning, Piercing and Slashing damage from weapons and bukijutsu that use weapons as a component.</p><p>• You have vulnerability to Earth and Fire damage.</p><p>• You can move across difficult terrain on solid ground without spending any extra movement, as you melt the obstructions in your path.</p><p>• The ground in a 10-foot radius around you is covered in acid, counts as difficult terrain for creatures other than you, and moves with you.</p><p>• You can use your action to blast a 15-foot cone of acid from you in a direction you choose. Each creature in the cone must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 4d8 Acid damage and gains 1 rank of the corroded condition on a failed save or half as much and no further effects on a successful one.</p>",
